# Boolean Lead Sheet and Checklist Conversion Layer

Structure every finding, task, rule, gap, fix, safeguard, improvement, workflow, repo standard, and recommendation so it can be converted into a checklist, audit sheet, tracker, repo issue, GitHub issue, GitLab issue, project board task, validation rule, or operational review sheet without rewriting.

Every point must be written as a testable statement.

Use Boolean-style framing wherever possible:

* Is this present? Yes / No
* Is this complete? Yes / No
* Is this tested? Yes / No
* Is this filed correctly? Yes / No
* Is this reusable? Yes / No
* Is this automated? Yes / No
* Is this safe? Yes / No
* Is this reviewed? Yes / No
* Is this approved? Yes / No
* Is this ready to ship? Yes / No
* Is this recoverable? Yes / No
* Is this traceable? Yes / No
* Is this assigned? Yes / No
* Is this validated? Yes / No

Do not write vague recommendations only.

Convert each recommendation into a clear Boolean test with a pass condition and fail condition.

Each checklist-ready item must include:

1. Item ID
2. Category
3. Requirement
4. Boolean Test
5. Pass Condition
6. Fail Condition
7. Status
8. Evidence Needed
9. Fix Needed
10. Owner / Role
11. Reviewer
12. Final Approval

Use this format when useful:

| Item ID | Category    | Requirement                       | Boolean Test              | Pass Condition                       | Fail Condition        | Status                | Evidence Needed | Fix Needed         | Owner / Role | Reviewer          | Final Approval |
